                  <handDesc><handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                    <seg type="rubrication">
                      <ref target="#ms_i1.1 #ms_i1.2 #ms_i1.3"/>
                      <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                      <ref target="#ms_i1.4 #ms_i1.5"/>
                      <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign></seg>
                      <desc>
                        In the ninth biblical canticle, <locus target="#110r" facs="222">fols. 110r, </locus>, every second line is written in red ink.
                        These lines contain the same basic content, though with slight variation
                        Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#102r" facs="206">102r, </locus> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#110v #111r" facs="224">110v, 111r</locus> (tenth biblical canticle)
                      </desc>
                    </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#64r" facs="130">Fol. 64r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1066DavidHarp">David Playing the Harp</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#1r" facs="004">fols. 1r, </locus> (colorful, ornate ḥaräg);
                      <locus target="#6v #91r" facs="015 184">6v, 91r, </locus> (multiple full stops);
                      <locus target="#6v #12r #18v #26r #31v #36v #43v #52r #58r #65r #76v #77r #88v #91v #97r #103r #114v #124v #125r" facs="015 026 039 054 065 075 089 106 118 155 156 179 185 196 208 231 251 252">6v, 12r, 18v, 26r, 31v, 36v, 43v, 52r, 58r, 65r, 76v, 77r, 88v, 91v, 97r, 103r, 114v, 124v, 125r</locus> (simple, black ḥaräg</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a1"><desc type="OwnershipNote"><locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001">Fol. ir(ecto)</locus> in red ink <q>“This Psalter belongs to Qes Räda Agǝdaw.”</q> See also the text after <locus target="#129v" facs="261">129v</locus></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e1"><desc><locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002">Fol. iv(erso)</locus> text illegible.</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e2"><desc><locus target="#48r" facs="098">Fol. 48r</locus>an intricate symbol in the fore edge margin and the writing of the line in red ink marks the midpoint of the Psalter. </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a2"><desc type="GuestText"><locus target="#112" facs="226">Fol. 112</locus> is a substitute folio with the <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2259salota#Isaiah">Song of
                                                  Isaiah, Isaiah</title>, the prophet on it</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a3"><desc><locus target="#128v" facs="259">Fol. 128v</locus> Note on <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3851Hassab">We have written a
                                                  computus that we will remember in order not to
                                                  congregate with apostates...</ref> </desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e3"><desc><locus target="#64v #128r #129r #129v" facs="131 258 260 261">Fols. 64v, 128r, 129r, 129v</locus> blank</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e4"><desc>
                        words of text are written interlinearly, <locus target="#60v #120r #123v" facs="123 242 149">folss. 60v, 120r, 123v, </locus>;
                        and lines of text are written interlinearly, <locus target="#21v #63r #110v" facs="045 128 223">21v, 63r, 110v, </locus>;
                        erasure markings are visible, <locus target="#38r #39v #40r #54v #75r" facs="078 081 082 111 152">38r, 39v, 40r, 54v, 75r, </locus>, etc.;
                        text has been removed, e.g., <locus target="#121r #123v" facs="244 149">121r, 123v</locus>.</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e6"><desc>The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection
                        of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe
                        reduces the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (throughout). This scribe also will complete the line of
                        text above the end of the line, e.g., <locus target="#80r #89r" facs="162 180">fols. 80r, 89r</locus>.</desc></item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
